laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring up to 13 mm and fluid filled with hyperemia. High-density material within may represent appendicolith. There is surrounding stranding of the fat in the right lower quadrant. The visualized lungs show mild atelectasis. The liver enhances homogenously without any focal lesions. The kidneys show tiny hypodensities likely cysts and a 1.4 x 1.3 cm hyperdense lesion likely a hyperdense cyst. No significant abnormalities in other abdominal organs.
